<div itemprop="articleBody">
<h3>Tutorial 24. Joining the Skirt with the Body of the Dress.</h3>
<p></p>
<p><strong>I turn out the skirt. </strong>&nbsp;</p>
<p>
<img src="https://corsetacademy.s3.amazonaws.com/wedding%20dresses/wedding%202/Tutorial%2024_files/image002.jpg" class="img-responsive center-block"></p>
<p><strong>And I insert the garment into it. </strong></p>
<p>
<img src="https://corsetacademy.s3.amazonaws.com/wedding%20dresses/wedding%202/Tutorial%2024_files/image004.jpg" class="img-responsive center-block"></p>
<p></p>
<p><strong>I match the centres at the front and pin the skirt to the dress in accordance with the markings.&nbsp; </strong></p>
<p>
<img src="https://corsetacademy.s3.amazonaws.com/wedding%20dresses/wedding%202/Tutorial%2024_files/image006.jpg" class="img-responsive center-block"></p>
<p>
<img src="https://corsetacademy.s3.amazonaws.com/wedding%20dresses/wedding%202/Tutorial%2024_files/image008.jpg" class="img-responsive center-block"></p>
<p></p>
<p>
<img src="https://corsetacademy.s3.amazonaws.com/wedding%20dresses/wedding%202/Tutorial%2024_files/image010.jpg" class="img-responsive center-block"></p>
<p>
<img src="https://corsetacademy.s3.amazonaws.com/wedding%20dresses/wedding%202/Tutorial%2024_files/image012.jpg" class="img-responsive center-block"></p>
<p></p>
<p>
<img src="https://corsetacademy.s3.amazonaws.com/wedding%20dresses/wedding%202/Tutorial%2024_files/image014.jpg" class="img-responsive center-block"></p>
<p><strong>The skirt is pinned together! The lengths of the skirt and the corset coincide.&nbsp; </strong></p>
<p><strong>I secure the skirt by machine-stitching. </strong></p>
<p><strong><br>
<img src="https://corsetacademy.s3.amazonaws.com/wedding%20dresses/wedding%202/Tutorial%2024_files/image016.jpg" class="img-responsive center-block"></strong></p>
<p><strong>And I turn it out again. </strong></p>
<p>
<img src="https://corsetacademy.s3.amazonaws.com/wedding%20dresses/wedding%202/Tutorial%2024_files/image018.jpg" class="img-responsive center-block"></p>
<p><strong>The skirt is full and bouffant - just the way we want it to be.&nbsp; </strong></p>
<p>
<img src="https://corsetacademy.s3.amazonaws.com/wedding%20dresses/wedding%202/Tutorial%2024_files/image020.jpg" class="img-responsive center-block"></p>
<p></p>
<p>
<img src="https://corsetacademy.s3.amazonaws.com/wedding%20dresses/wedding%202/Tutorial%2024_files/image022.jpg" class="img-responsive center-block"></p>
<p></p>
<p>
<img src="https://corsetacademy.s3.amazonaws.com/wedding%20dresses/wedding%202/Tutorial%2024_files/image024.jpg" class="img-responsive center-block"></p>
<p><strong>We need to apply some final touches to the hem: </strong>mark the shape of the hem on the face of the skirt, trim it, overlock the edge, and turn it up by the overlock seam width. </p>
<p><strong>I'd like to show you how I finish the hem of the dress after using the overlock machine. </strong></p>
<p><strong>I turn up the hem. </strong></p>
<p>
<img src="https://corsetacademy.s3.amazonaws.com/wedding%20dresses/wedding%202/Tutorial%2024_files/image026.jpg" class="img-responsive center-block"></p>
<p><strong>And I stitch close to the edge<em> over the face side</em>. </strong>You should press the garment afterwards.&nbsp; </p>
<p>
<img src="https://corsetacademy.s3.amazonaws.com/wedding%20dresses/wedding%202/Tutorial%2024_files/image028.jpg" class="img-responsive center-block"></p>
<p></p>
<p>
<img src="https://corsetacademy.s3.amazonaws.com/wedding%20dresses/wedding%202/Tutorial%2024_files/image030.jpg" class="img-responsive center-block"></p>
<p></p>
<p>
<img src="https://corsetacademy.s3.amazonaws.com/wedding%20dresses/wedding%202/Tutorial%2024_files/image032.jpg" class="img-responsive center-block"></p>
<p><strong>Now we can decorate our dress.</strong></p>
<p><strong>&nbsp;</strong></p>

</div> <!-- Itemprop END: articleBody -->
